  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Tuesday, and my living room is currently a robot factory.",
      "zh": "星期二，我家客廳現在是一座機器人工廠。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William's newest obsession is giant robots, after his old obsession with knights lasted exactly one month.",
      "zh": "William 最新的迷戀對象是巨大機器人，他上一個迷戀對象騎士只維持了一個月。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He decided he needed a real robot costume, so he collected every empty box, pipe, and button he could find in the house.",
      "zh": "他決定他需要一套真正的機器人裝，所以把家裡每個空盒子、水管跟按鈕都收集起來。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He used a roll of tape and a long piece of rope to attach two boxes to his arms like giant metal hands.",
      "zh": "他用一卷膠帶跟一條長繩子，把兩個盒子綁在手臂上，變成兩隻巨大的金屬手。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Then he painted the boxes silver with Mom's old paint, which he was absolutely not supposed to touch.",
      "zh": "接著他用媽媽的舊油漆把盒子漆成銀色，而那罐油漆他根本不該碰。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Perry walked straight through the wet paint and left small silver footprints across the whole living room floor.",
      "zh": "Perry 直接踩過那些還沒乾的油漆，在整個客廳地板上留下一串小小的銀色腳印。"
    },
    {
      "en": "When Mom saw the silver footprints, William immediately said, \"That was Perry's fault, not mine.\"",
      "zh": "媽媽看到那些銀色腳印時，William 馬上說：「那是 Perry 的錯，不是我的。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "I pointed out that Perry does not know how to use a paint can, so someone had to open it for him.",
      "zh": "我指出 Perry 根本不會開油漆罐，所以一定是有人幫他開的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William got quiet for a second, then admitted the whole robot costume was his own idea from the start.",
      "zh": "William 安靜了一秒，然後承認整套機器人裝從頭到尾都是他自己的主意。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mom was angry about the paint, but she also laughed a little at how much effort a seven-year-old put into a cardboard robot.",
      "zh": "媽媽對油漆的事很生氣，但也忍不住笑了，一個七歲小孩竟然為了一套紙箱機器人這麼努力。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William had to clean the floor himself with a wet towel, complaining the whole time that giant robots do not do chores.",
      "zh": "William 得自己用濕毛巾把地板擦乾淨，一邊擦一邊抱怨說巨大機器人才不做家事。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I told him that even giant robots probably have a button somewhere that says \"clean the floor,\" and he actually stopped to think about that.",
      "zh": "我跟他說，就算是巨大機器人身上大概也有一個寫著「打掃地板」的按鈕，他還真的停下來想了一下。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Once the floor was dry again, William put his robot costume back on and marched around the house making machine sounds.",
      "zh": "地板乾了以後，William 又把機器人裝穿回去，在家裡到處走來走去發出機器的聲音。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He knocked his elbow on a table and yelled that even giant robots feel pain sometimes, which made Sophia laugh from the kitchen.",
      "zh": "他的手肘撞到桌子，大喊就算是巨大機器人有時候也會覺得痛，這讓在廚房的 Sophia 笑了出來。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia told him a real story about a farmer who built his own simple machine out of wood a long time ago.",
      "zh": "Sophia 跟他說了一個真實故事，很久以前有個農夫用木頭自己造了一台簡單的機器。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William's eyes got wide and he asked if the farmer's machine could also turn into a robot with laser arms.",
      "zh": "William 眼睛睜得大大的，問那個農夫的機器能不能也變成有雷射手臂的機器人。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia said probably not, but the farmer's machine helped carry heavy things, which is still pretty useful.",
      "zh": "Sophia 說大概不行，但那台機器能幫忙搬重物，這件事本身其實也很有用。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William thought about that for a moment and decided his robot's real job would be carrying his backpack to school.",
      "zh": "William 想了一下，決定他的機器人真正的工作就是幫他背書包上學。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I explained that a cardboard robot cannot walk to school, and he looked at me like I had ruined his whole plan.",
      "zh": "我跟他解釋紙箱機器人沒辦法走去學校，他看我的表情好像我毀了他整個計畫。"
    },
    {
      "en": "At dinner, William kept both cardboard arms on and tried to eat rice with a fork taped to a box.",
      "zh": "吃晚餐的時候，William 兩隻紙箱手臂都還穿著，還試著用綁在盒子上的叉子吃飯。"
    },
    {
      "en": "It did not work at all, and he finally gave up and took the boxes off so he could eat with his real hands.",
      "zh": "結果完全行不通，他最後只好放棄，把盒子拿下來用自己真正的手吃飯。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Dad came home late, saw the robot costume sitting by the door, and asked if we were building an actual robot in this house.",
      "zh": "爸爸很晚才回家，看到門邊放著那套機器人裝，問我們是不是在家裡造真的機器人。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William proudly said yes, and that the robot's only weakness right now was stairs, dinner, and homework.",
      "zh": "William 驕傲地說是，而且這個機器人目前唯一的弱點是樓梯、晚餐，還有功課。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Dad laughed so hard he had to sit down, and even I had to admit that was a pretty good joke for a seven-year-old.",
      "zh": "爸爸笑到必須坐下來，就連我也不得不承認，這對一個七歲小孩來說是個不錯的笑話。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Before bed, William asked if I would write about his robot in my diary, so other people could know about it someday.",
      "zh": "睡前 William 問我會不會把他的機器人寫進我的日記裡，這樣以後其他人才會知道這件事。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I told him I just did, and his whole face lit up like he had just become a little bit famous.",
      "zh": "我跟他說我剛剛已經寫好了，他整張臉瞬間亮了起來，好像他剛剛變得有點小有名氣一樣。"
    }
  ],
